Ready for some enui inducing meta-discussion?
The way this game is set up, requires that people be killed off through voting and lynching to gain information about allegiances.
Well there are more sources:
1. Roles that follow people;
(seer, harlot, stalker...)
2. Role that check the dead
3. Voting pattern
4. Chat log (less rigid)
Unfortunately the former (1-3) require nights to have elapsed, action to have taken place and people to have died before this information begins to emerge.
Once you have some information, it fuels number 4.
The downside is a quiet night or two, before the game really spools up - unless of course you have a seer hit bullseye night one
Where I'm going with this is I wonder if it would be possible to pre-load the game with some information, run a dummy night, or simulate a dummy night.
This could randomly (or through user input) generate the visits and results of for a Night Zero.
